traceroute Command
What is traceroute?
traceroute shows the path (hops) that packets take from your machine to a destination server.

It helps you understand:



Where the network is slow

Where the connection is failing

How many routers are between you and the target




Basic command
traceroute google.com 

Example output
1  192.168.1.1     1.2 ms
2  10.10.0.1       5.4 ms
3  72.14.233.21    20.1 ms
4  142.250.183.14  22.3 ms 

How to read it
Each line = one hop (router).

Numbers on the right = latency (time taken).

  * = no response from that hop.




