Reflection
Fastest command when something is broken: ping gives the quickest signal on connectivity; ip route tells you where the packet would even try to go.

If routing looks wrong: check the Internet layer (routing table, default gateway), then the Link layer (ARP — is the gateway's MAC even resolved?).

If a service is unreachable but the host pings fine: the issue is at the Transport/Application layer — check the listening port with ss -tulpn and the service logs.

Two follow-up checks in a real incident: systemctl status <service> and journalctl -u <service> -n 50.

